JOHANNESBBURG - South Africa s top-ranked Kevin Anderson continued his slide in the world ratings as he fell three spots to 79th in ATP singles rankings released on Monday.The strong-serving Anderson achieved a career-high 10th ranking in October 2015.READ: SA's Anderson breaks into world top 10SA s number two singles player, Lloyd Harris also dropped three places to 280th.On the doubles side, Raven Klaasen moved down one place to 13th in the rankings.Chanel Simmonds is the top South African on the women s singles rankings at 331st. Simmonds is also the top women s doubles player at 221st. African News Agency